<page>
   <topic>UI_GET_IMAGE_FILENAME Function</topic>
   <syntax>OutputString as C = ui_get_image_filename([C filename [,C imagetype ]])</syntax>
   <arguments>
     <argument>
         <name>filename</name>
         <description>Optional. The filename of an image file.
</description>
     </argument>
     <argument>
         <name>imagetype</name>
         <description>Character</description>
     </argument>
   </arguments>
   <discussion>
The UI_GET_IMAGE_FILENAME() function prompts for an image filename (.bmp or .jpg) and displays an image browser. 
   </discussion>
    <sections>
       <section>
           <figure><link>images/UI_GET_IMAGE_FILENAME.gif</link></figure>
       </section>
      
      
       <section>
            <description>Limitations: Desktop applications only.
</description>
         
       </section>
   </sections>
   <sections>
       <section>
            <title>Example</title>
            <example><![CDATA[
? ui_get_image_filename()
= "C:\Wallpaper\chester\Crust Cake.bmp"
]]></example>
       </section>
   </sections>
